{"descriptions":[{"id":1367,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThis is the most polite form in which to phrase a command or a request. It is used only with honorifics, and takes the present-future (not the imperative) form of the verb.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཕེབས་རོགས་གནང་།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Please go,\u0026rdquo; or \u0026ldquo;Please come.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགསུངས་རོགས་གནང་།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Please say.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཞུགས་རོགས་གནང་།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Please stay.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམཆོད་རོགས་གནང་།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Please eat.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཀག་རོགས་གནང་།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Please stop (the car, the dog, etc.).\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཞུ་རོགས་གནང་།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Please ask.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eNote\u003c/em\u003e: There is also the non-honorific version \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརོགས་བྱེད་\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:44 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:44 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}